ccurl - Simple HTTP Client for TROPIX
======================================

A minimal curl-like HTTP client written in C using TROPIX libc and XTI.

FEATURES
--------
- Download files via HTTP (no HTTPS support)
- Output to stdout or save to file
- Simple command-line interface

BUILDING
--------
make

USAGE
-----
ccurl [-v] [-o file] <url>

OPTIONS
-------
-v        Verbose mode
-o file   Save output to file instead of stdout

EXAMPLES
--------
Download to stdout:
  ccurl http://example.com/index.html

Save to file:
  ccurl -o index.html http://example.com/index.html

Verbose mode:
  ccurl -v http://example.com/

LIMITATIONS
-----------
- HTTP only (no HTTPS)
- HTTP/1.0 protocol
- No authentication support
- No redirect following
- Basic error handling

IMPLEMENTATION
--------------
Uses TROPIX XTI (X/Open Transport Interface) via /dev/itntcp for TCP connections.
Based on the www client in cmd/itnet/www.
